@Node "WhatUse" "What I Used"
@Prev "Legal"
@Next "Thanks"

@{bd "What I Used"}

@{fg shine}BED@{fg text} - @{b}Black's Editor@{ub}, to write @{bl "LhA2LZX"} and also this  @{b}AmigaGuide@{ub} doc.  It is
	@{i}not@{ui}  your average  @{b}PD@{ub} editor,  so @{b}get it  soon!@{ub}  It allows  you to edit
	@{b}text/binary@{ub} files, has a @{b}user-configurable menu bar@{ub}, has a multitude of
	@{b}AREXX macros@{ub} (and you can  add your own) and can do just about @{i}anything@{ui}
	you  require - @{b}justification, clipboard support, encryption@{ub}  &  @{b}viewing
	individual  @{i}AmigaGuide@{ui}  pages as you write them@{ub}  are just a  few of the
	options!

@{fg shine}DiskSqueeze@{fg text} -an @{b}AmigaDOS@{ub} @{"script" link Scripts} file which uses @{b}LZX@{ub} to compress @{b}entire disks@{ub}
	and so giving better compression than @{b}DMS@{ub}! It also allows a filelist to
	be added  to the archive,  so that you know exactly  which files are on
	the disk. @{b}DiskSqueeze@{ub} helped me to understand how to structure a script
	file (although originally it was by messing around with @{"DMSMaker" link Also 17} that I
	learnt how to write scripts) and gave me a few ideas to improve @{bl "LhA2LZX"}
	(for  instance using the  @{b}Which@{ub} command,  checking @{b}memory size@{ub} and most
	notably about the use of @{"Environment Variables" link Env}).

@{fg shine}DOSMan@{fg text} - An @{b}AmigaDOS@{ub} reference manual  (in @{b}AmigaGuide@{ub} and @{b}MUI@{ub} format)  which
	details the usage of commands @{b}up to and including the new WB 3.1  ones@{ub},
	and gives examples of how to use them.@{i}@{b}Invaluable@{ui}@{ub} if you don't have one,
	and essential  to find out what all the  @{"CLI" link CLI} commands do and how to use
	them.

@{i}And, of course ...@{ui}

@{"LhA" link LhA} Evaluation V1.51		
@{"LZX" link LZX} 1.21 (Evaluation) Archive/Extract utility - 68020/68030 Version.

@Endnode

